==== M569.3: Read Motor Driver Encoder ====
{{Firmware Support | fived={{no}} | teacup={{no}} | sprinter={{no}} | marlin={{no}} | prusa={{no}} | repetier={{no}} | smoothie={{no}} | reprapfirmware={{yes}}<sup>1</sup> | klipper={{no}} | bfb={{no}} | machinekit={{no}} | makerbot={{no}} | redeem={{no}} | mk4duo={{no}} | yaskawa={{no}} | grbl={{no}} }}

This causes the RepRap machine to report its current motor encoder positions to the host.

;Parameters
:<code>Pn</code> or <code>Pn.n</code> Motor driver number, or board address and driver number. Several drivers may be specified, separated by colon, or by specifying a sequence of P parameters.

If no parameters are supplied, then empty brackets are returned.

;Examples
 M569.3
<tt>[],</tt>
 M569.3 P0:1:2:3
<tt>[-155.28, -4089.60, 6842.04, 0.00, ],</tt>
 M569.3 P3:1 P2 P3
<tt>[0.00, -4089.60, 6842.04, -155.28, ],</tt>

;Notes
<sup>1</sup> Planned for RepRapFirmware 3.4.
